qas.question: When did the Ann Arbor news end its print?
Which was the only city in the US to loose its only daily paper?
What online newspaper stopped printing in 2009?
What newspaper covered local news until September 13, 2014?
When did the Ann Arbor Paper start a limited print publication?

context: <b3_0><b4_0>The Ann Arbor News<b4_0/><b3_0/>, owned by the Michigan-based <a0_0>Booth Newspapers<a0_0/> chain, is the major daily newspaper serving Ann Arbor and the rest of Washtenaw County. The newspaper ended its 174-year print run in <a1_0>2009<a1_0/>, due to economic difficulties. It was replaced by AnnArbor.com, but returned to a limited print publication under its former name in <b6_0>2013<b6_0/>. Another Ann Arbor-based publication that has ceased production was the Ann Arbor Paper, a free monthly. <a2_0>Ann Arbor<a2_0/> has been said to be the first significant city to lose its only daily paper. <b5_0>The Ann Arbor Chronicle<b5_0/>, an online newspaper, covered local news, including meetings of the library board, county commission, and DDA until September 3, 2014.
